rows.label: tlk41700121_02_msg0001
rows.name:
So Gula's been under Superbian rule
for nearly 50 years now, huh...

rows.label: tlk41700121_02_msg0002
rows.name:
Gula used to have its own army, you
know. My dad was an officer there. Not
that you'd know it to look at him now.

rows.label: tlk41700121_02_msg0003
rows.name:
After Gula was defeated, the army
was disbanded, and all we have now
are small defense corps for each tribe.

rows.label: tlk41700121_02_msg0004
rows.name:
It may seem we're being oppressed,
but if you look at it another way, we're
also under Superbia's protection.

rows.label: tlk41700121_02_msg0005
rows.name:
The Superbians don't really interfere
with our culture. That's something to
be grateful for, if you ask me.
